the subscriber you dialed

41
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:25,300
can not be connected for the moment.

42
00:02:25,633 --> 00:02:26,833
Please redial later.

43
00:02:34,667 --> 00:02:35,533
Sorry

44
00:02:35,867 --> 00:02:37,067
the subscriber you dialed

45
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:38,433
can not be connected for the moment.

46
00:02:38,767 --> 00:02:40,000
Please dial later.

47
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:40,667
Sorry

48
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:42,033
the subscriber you dialed...

49
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:52,967
Thanks.

50
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:11,700
Why are you here?

51
00:03:14,067 --> 00:03:15,233
I don't feel like going to school suddenly

52
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,800
and want to know what it feels like to skip classes.

53
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:48,767
I will always be with you

54
00:04:51,033 --> 00:04:52,033
no matter what.

55
00:05:36,467 --> 00:05:41,033
[Episode 6]
[I Will Always Be with You]

56
00:05:47,567 --> 00:05:48,233
[3079 days]

57
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:51,667
[The seventeenth day of officially living together]

58
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:53,133
Anyway, in conclusion

59
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:55,067
everyone's work has been fairly good

60
00:05:55,267 --> 00:05:56,600
this year.

61
00:05:57,233 --> 00:05:58,267
It's just barely passing, though.

62
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:00,667
I hope everyone

63
00:06:00,667 --> 00:06:02,233
will continue to strive hard next year.

64
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:06,833
It's time for the most troublesome issue of the year again.

65
00:06:09,467 --> 00:06:10,633
Who will be on duty

66
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:12,167
during the Spring Festival?

67
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,433
Is there any volunteer

68
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:18,767
who will impress me?

69
00:06:24,567 --> 00:06:25,733
You all keep silent?

70
00:06:26,567 --> 00:06:27,133
Okay.

71
00:06:27,767 --> 00:06:28,933
Then I'll call names.

72
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:32,000
Su Tian?

73
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,867
Ms. Qian, I...

74
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:37,000
Oh, right.

75
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:38,133
I forgot.

76
00:06:38,133 --> 00:06:39,667
Take a good rest then.

77
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:40,800
Thank you, Ms. Qian.

78
00:06:43,933 --> 00:06:44,667
Zhen Yu

79
00:06:45,233 --> 00:06:47,200
I remember that you are from Nanwu.

80
00:06:47,467 --> 00:06:48,800
So you don't have to go out of town.

81
00:06:48,933 --> 00:06:50,133
Could you stay on duty?

82
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:50,933
Mr. Qian

83
00:06:50,933 --> 00:06:52,300
I bought the ticket to Hainan long ago

84
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:53,767
and will celebrate the Spring Festival there.

85
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,500
I've even bought some dresses.

86
00:06:55,733 --> 00:06:57,200
You are going to celebrate the Spring Festival in Hainan?

87
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,767
You are really rich.

88
00:06:58,933 --> 00:07:00,367
I bought it long ago. It was not expensive.

89
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:03,833
Fu Zhuang

90
00:07:04,667 --> 00:07:05,467
stop hiding.

91
00:07:05,867 --> 00:07:07,067
I've seen you.

92
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:08,267
Ms. Qian, I...

93
00:07:08,433 --> 00:07:10,200
I have been out of home for two years.

94
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:11,367
Stay with your mother then.

95
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:12,833
Thank you, Ms. Qian.

96
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:13,933
Wu Mian?

97
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:15,667
Ms. Qian

98
00:07:15,867 --> 00:07:17,833
I have to go home for a blind date this year.

99
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:19,400
My mom has arranged it for me.

100
00:07:19,667 --> 00:07:20,767
I won't be back until the eighth day of the Spring Festival.

101
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:21,467
Just lock the door.

102
00:07:21,467 --> 00:07:23,467
Help finish the food in the refrigerator.

103
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:24,067
Thanks.

104
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:27,933
Ms. Qian

105
00:07:28,167 --> 00:07:29,600
I can stay on duty.

106
00:07:29,867 --> 00:07:31,233
I don't have anything else to do anyway.

107
00:07:32,133 --> 00:07:33,433
You see?

108
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,133
Look how responsible Yifan is!

109
00:07:35,133 --> 00:07:37,167
You guys need to learn from her.

110
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,867
Thank you for your hard work, Yifan.

111
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,400
Okay, stop working.

112
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,167
Everyone is so busy.

113
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:49,733
You are not going home for the Spring Festival?

114
00:07:52,067 --> 00:07:52,933
Su Haoan!

115
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:55,367
Where are you, Su Haoan?

116
00:07:55,367 --> 00:07:56,233
Su Haoan!

117
00:07:57,633 --> 00:07:58,633
Su Haoan!

118
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:00,500
Come here!

119
00:08:06,167 --> 00:08:07,500
What orders did you place?

120
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:10,300
What's wrong?

121
00:08:11,167 --> 00:08:12,467
Why did you keep sending me orders?

122
00:08:12,467 --> 00:08:14,467
[Go home with Su Haoan during the Spring Festival]

123
00:08:14,767 --> 00:08:15,833
Don't you take all kinds of orders?

124
00:08:15,933 --> 00:08:16,933
Of course not!

125
00:08:17,067 --> 00:08:18,367
What else do you want me to do except have dinner?

126
00:08:19,567 --> 00:08:20,200
You can

127
00:08:20,567 --> 00:08:21,300
pretend to be my girlfriend.

128
00:08:22,567 --> 00:08:24,667
Pretend to be your girlfriend?

129
00:08:24,767 --> 00:08:26,633
Our platform strictly prohibits pornography, gambling and...

130
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:28,733
You guys

131
00:08:29,033 --> 00:08:29,733
just go on.

132
00:08:29,733 --> 00:08:30,667
Keep eating and drinking.

133
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:31,633
It's fine.

134
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,200
What's fine?

135
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:33,833
We haven't seen each other for a long time.

136
00:08:34,167 --> 00:08:35,233
Why are you talking so loudly?

137
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,367
Where are we going?

138
00:08:36,633 --> 00:08:38,067
Let's go upstairs and talk about it.

139
00:08:40,067 --> 00:08:40,867
Take your seat.

140
00:08:41,433 --> 00:08:42,033
Tell me.

141
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:43,600
Drink some water first.

142
00:08:43,767 --> 00:08:44,500
Don't be mad.

143
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:45,867
Tell me now!

144
00:08:46,267 --> 00:08:47,067
Here's the thing.

145
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:48,433
My grandpa and grandma had a fight.

146
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:49,733
My grandma went on a self-driving tour out of anger

147
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:51,333
and, it has been for almost a year.

148
00:08:51,633 --> 00:08:52,600
She said she wouldn't be home

149
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,133
for the Spring Festival

150
00:08:54,267 --> 00:08:55,500
if I didn't bring home a girlfriend.

151
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:56,433
So I'm wondering...

152
00:08:56,433 --> 00:08:57,233
I won't play.

153
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:58,167
I didn't finish.

154
00:08:58,233 --> 00:08:59,467
You want me to pretend to be your lover, right?

155
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:00,033
Yes.

156
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:00,633
I won't accept it.

157
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:01,200
Why?

158
00:09:01,233 --> 00:09:01,967
It's awkward.

159
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:02,967
Because I never take a job

160
00:09:02,967 --> 00:09:03,900
of pretending to be someone's girlfriend.

161
00:09:04,067 --> 00:09:05,600
Just help me as I'm your best friend.

162
00:09:05,967 --> 00:09:07,200
It's awkward because it's you.

163
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:10,433
So you can do it

164
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:11,233
for someone else?

165
00:09:23,967 --> 00:09:24,867
Here, look!

166
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,733
Who's J?

167
00:09:29,867 --> 00:09:30,867
It's Jun.

168
00:09:31,067 --> 00:09:31,667
He's a chef.

169
00:09:31,867 --> 00:09:33,067
"Someone else" doesn't mean

170
00:09:33,067 --> 00:09:34,767
I can do it if someone else places the order.

171
00:09:34,767 --> 00:09:35,600
Then who should place the order?

172
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,133
It requires me to pretend to be YOUR girlfriend anyway.

173
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:38,800
You said you could do it for someone else.

174
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,467
You will

175
00:09:40,467 --> 00:09:41,667
make my account blocked

176
00:09:41,667 --> 00:09:42,433
for brushing scams

177
00:09:42,433 --> 00:09:43,200
by doing this.

178
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,233
Cancel them now!

179
00:09:47,433 --> 00:09:48,133
Well

180
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,600
guys, cancel the order if you have placed one.

181
00:09:50,267 --> 00:09:51,467
Don't place any orders if you haven't yet.

182
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:52,367
I'll still treat you to drinks.

183
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:53,367
Thanks.

184
00:09:55,167 --> 00:09:56,033
Let's make it clear

185
00:09:56,633 --> 00:09:57,767
that I'll help you as a friend.

186
00:09:57,767 --> 00:09:59,433
But I won't do anything only a girlfriend can do.

187
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:00,867
Okay. I won't do anything like that either.

188
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:02,233
Come on. Let's go downstairs.

189
00:10:02,233 --> 00:10:03,600
I'll treat you to drinks and food.

190
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:05,000
It's my apology.

191
00:10:05,367 --> 00:10:05,933
Let's go.

192
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:09,833
Come on.

193
00:10:10,367 --> 00:10:11,600
- What? - Didn't I say I couldn't?

194
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:12,967
Excuse me!

195
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:22,233
[On the Spring Festival Eve]
Five, four, three, two, one!

196
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:26,867
Are you okay?

197
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:27,567
Yes.

198
00:10:27,567 --> 00:10:29,200
Who wants a red envelope?

199
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,400
- Here! - Come on!

200
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:33,667
- Come on! - Happy New Year!

201
00:10:33,667 --> 00:10:34,467
Come on! Here!

202
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:35,367
You two take these.

203
00:10:35,367 --> 00:10:36,167
I'll grab some more.

204
00:10:36,567 --> 00:10:37,200
Thank you.

205
00:10:38,233 --> 00:10:39,000
You are welcome.

206
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,133
Don't hustle.

207
00:10:40,133 --> 00:10:40,867
Be careful.

208
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:42,033
Yifan

209
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:43,800
can you do it on your own?

210
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,800
I can be here at any time

211
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,200
if you need me.

212
00:10:46,567 --> 00:10:47,567
Don't worry, Tian.

213
00:10:47,567 --> 00:10:48,900
Just go back for the Spring Festival.

214
00:10:49,133 --> 00:10:50,133
Your baby needs to rest

215
00:10:50,133 --> 00:10:51,000
even if you don't.

216
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,500
I left the baby's father but kept the baby

217
00:10:55,733 --> 00:10:56,833
and will be a single mother.

218
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:59,233
I don't know whether my decision

219
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:00,667
is right or wrong.

220
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:02,400
Or is all of this

221
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,733
an arbitrary act?

222
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:07,400
Do you think my kid

223
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,267
will ask me where their dad is

224
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:09,167
in the future Spring Festivals?

225
00:11:11,067 --> 00:11:12,633
Don't think too much.

226
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:13,900
Children nowadays

227
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:15,667
are much more open-minded than us.

228
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:16,900
Also

229
00:11:17,267 --> 00:11:19,200
the vision of love now is different.

230
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,567
Don't cry.

231
00:11:22,767 --> 00:11:24,400
I am touched by you.

232
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:26,733
I believe

233
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,200
you will bring a bright future

234
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,200
for the baby.

235
00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:30,833
That's for sure.

236
00:11:31,367 --> 00:11:32,033
Don't cry.

237
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:33,800
Come on!

238
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:34,667
I'm back.

239
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:35,500
Here.

240
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,267
Why are you crying?

241
00:11:37,267 --> 00:11:38,833
I'm moved by what you did.

242
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:40,300
Look at you.

243
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,067
Is someone bullying you?

244
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,167
No.

245
00:11:42,733 --> 00:11:43,967
This is for the baby.

246
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:45,400
Thank you.

247
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:46,333
Yifan

248
00:11:46,733 --> 00:11:47,833
thank you for staying on duty.

249
00:11:47,967 --> 00:11:50,033
Be happy every day in the coming year.

250
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:51,567
Thank you.

251
00:11:59,367 --> 00:12:02,567
[AUSPICIOUSNESS FROM THE GOLDEN LOONG]

252
00:12:02,567 --> 00:12:05,767
[BLESSINGS FOR THE NEW YEAR]

253
00:12:24,267 --> 00:12:25,467
You didn't go home, Mr. Zhang?

254
00:12:26,433 --> 00:12:27,600
Why did you leave so late?

255
00:12:28,567 --> 00:12:29,367
I'm on duty.

256
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:30,567
Will you still be here in a few days?

257
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:31,600
I will be here next few days.

258
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,833
Knock on my door if you need help.

259
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:34,400
You won't go home for the Spring Festival either?

260
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,333
Someone has to guard the TV station.

261
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:37,800
It's hard to be on duty alone.

262
00:12:38,467 --> 00:12:40,433
- Take this. - You are too kind.

263
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:41,333
Just take it.

264
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:42,967
Dad, when will jiaozi be ready?

265
00:12:42,967 --> 00:12:43,800
I'm hungry.

266
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:45,800
Be a good girl and check it yourself.

267
00:12:47,667 --> 00:12:48,900
I am not alone.

268
00:12:49,067 --> 00:12:50,633
My wife and daughter

269
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,133
came from our hometown to stay with me.

270
00:12:52,633 --> 00:12:53,167
About this

271
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:54,000
madam

272
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,433
just keep it for yourself.

273
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:57,000
No need to be polite with me.

274
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,067
Keep it for the kid.

275
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:00,033
Here.

276
00:13:00,467 --> 00:13:01,200
Jelly!

277
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,133
My favorite!

278
00:13:03,267 --> 00:13:04,200
Thank you.

279
00:13:05,867 --> 00:13:07,133
Come in and have some jiaozi.

280
00:13:07,233 --> 00:13:08,367
No, thanks. I have things to do.

281
00:13:08,700 --> 00:13:09,200
Okay.

282
00:13:09,567 --> 00:13:10,267
Happy New Year!

283
00:13:10,667 --> 00:13:11,467
Happy New Year!

284
00:13:16,067 --> 00:13:17,167
Here, your favorite

285
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:17,867
