286
00:13:22,167 --> 00:13:23,333
Zhang, try one.

287
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:27,933
Let's eat jiaozi!

288
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:54,633
Are you ready?

289
00:13:54,867 --> 00:13:55,867
Yes!

290
00:13:56,433 --> 00:13:57,000
Wait a moment.

291
00:13:59,467 --> 00:14:01,367
The wine is ready.

292
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:03,133
The ceremony is about to begin.

293
00:14:03,367 --> 00:14:03,967
Raise your glass.

294
00:14:04,633 --> 00:14:07,200
One, two, three...

295
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:08,633
Cheers!

296
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:11,800
Happy New Year!

297
00:14:13,133 --> 00:14:14,233
Happy New Year, Dian!

298
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,133
Happy New Year, Dian!

299
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:16,967
Happy New Year!

300
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,833
- Why is Yifan alone? - Well, Grandpa...

301
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:22,367
Welcome

302
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:25,467
to the Spring Festival Gala group chat conference.

303
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:28,433
Dian

304
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:31,167
say hello to Qiao.

305
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:33,767
- Happy New Year, Dian! - Happy New Year!

306
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:07,333
Is it that funny?

307
00:15:07,767 --> 00:15:08,867
It depends on the audience's mood

308
00:15:08,867 --> 00:15:10,633
whether the sketch is funny or not.

309
00:15:11,033 --> 00:15:12,767
You should be happy for the Spring Festival.

310
00:15:29,133 --> 00:15:29,833
Qiao

311
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:31,233
come eat jiaozi.

312
00:15:31,367 --> 00:15:32,200
Thank you, grandma.

313
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,167
Did you eat jiaozi, Dian?

314
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:36,167
Not yet.

315
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,133
You have to eat jiaozi for the Spring Festival.

316
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:39,033
Will you cook some yourself

317
00:15:39,033 --> 00:15:40,033
or order a takeaway?

318
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:41,333
We're going to set off firecrackers.

319
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:42,567
Hurry up, Qiao!

320
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:43,600
Let's go out to set off firecrackers.

321
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:45,733
I'm going to set off firecrackers now.

322
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:46,667
Talk to you later.

323
00:15:46,667 --> 00:15:47,167
Bye!

324
00:15:56,967 --> 00:15:57,800
Jiaozi

325
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,633
the taste of reunion.

326
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:02,367
I forgot to buy jiaozi.

327
00:16:29,633 --> 00:16:30,733
Why are you back?

328
00:16:32,067 --> 00:16:33,500
Didn't you tell me you wouldn't be back

329
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:34,500
until the eighth day of the Spring Festival?

330
00:16:35,133 --> 00:16:36,633
Too many relatives at home.

331
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:37,500
There are not enough rooms.

332
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,633
Happy New Year!

333
00:16:42,667 --> 00:16:43,500
Happy New Year!

334
00:16:45,667 --> 00:16:47,433
- It's mine! - What are you doing?

335
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:01,167
Come home for dinner!

336
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:02,033
What time is it?

337
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:03,900
Will you have the Spring Festival Eve's dinner or not?

338
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:27,000
Didn't you have the Spring Festival Eve's dinner?

339
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:05,533
Wen Yifan.

340
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:14,367
What's wrong?

341
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,067
I cooked too much.

342
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:18,900
Help eat some.

343
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:25,800
I'll help you put the rest in the refrigerator.

344
00:18:34,867 --> 00:18:35,667
Leave the vegetables here.

345
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:37,767
The meatballs...

346
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:38,467
Won't you eat them?

347
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,533
Put some in

348
00:18:40,533 --> 00:18:41,367
if you want to eat them.

349
00:18:42,167 --> 00:18:42,767
Okay.

350
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:50,933
Should we put in some jiaozi?

351
00:18:51,467 --> 00:18:52,367
It's the Spring Festival Eve.

352
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:55,433
Okay.

353
00:18:56,367 --> 00:18:57,267
Then put some in.

354
00:18:59,000 --> 00:18:59,800
Give me two eggs.

355
00:19:09,067 --> 00:19:10,900
Did you put in a whole pack of noodles?

356
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:12,867
So?

357
00:19:17,367 --> 00:19:19,400
I probably can't help you with too much.

358
00:19:20,267 --> 00:19:20,867
What?

359
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:23,567
I'm not very hungry.

360
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:24,900
I know.

361
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:33,133
The noodles you cooked

362
00:19:37,867 --> 00:19:39,033
are pretty tasty.

363
00:19:42,767 --> 00:19:43,767
Your expression

364
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:45,900
will make people think I intoxicated you.

365
00:19:48,267 --> 00:19:49,800
I didn't know you could cook.

366
00:19:50,767 --> 00:19:52,333
Is there anything I can't do?

367
00:19:53,067 --> 00:19:54,033
Aren't there a lot?

368
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:54,800
Such as?

369
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:56,333
Such as

370
00:19:58,567 --> 00:19:59,933
cooking noodles for just one person.

371
00:20:06,933 --> 00:20:07,767
Aren't you hungry?

372
00:20:07,767 --> 00:20:08,667
Why don't you eat?

373
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:11,400
I'll eat later.

374
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,433
It's a little weird

375
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,000
for you to stare at me while I eat.

376
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,767
It's the Spring Festival Eve today.

377
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:34,467
So it should be a reunion dinner.

378
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,933
We should eat together.

379
00:20:55,367 --> 00:20:57,633
♪I like you very much♪

380
00:20:57,633 --> 00:20:58,933
Do you have a name for the noodles?

381
00:21:03,533 --> 00:21:05,433
Noodles of wealth, longevity

382
00:21:07,233 --> 00:21:07,767
and richness.

383
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,533
No wonder there is jiaozi.

384
00:21:12,933 --> 00:21:16,667
♪Like a long passed mysterious love spell♪

385
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,267
Thanks to you

386
00:21:20,533 --> 00:21:21,767
I'm having jiaozi.

387
00:21:25,633 --> 00:21:27,767
Today Sang Yan and I

388
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:30,467
have our first dinner together alone after our reunion.

389
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,867
The Spring Festival Gala has young faces.

390
00:21:53,467 --> 00:21:55,233
So whether the show is good or not

391
00:21:55,467 --> 00:21:56,633
depends on whom you watch the show with.

392
00:22:11,767 --> 00:22:17,167
[Happy New Year]

393
00:22:22,767 --> 00:22:23,900
[Zhao Yuandong invites you to a video call]

394
00:22:28,167 --> 00:22:28,900
Jiang

395
00:22:29,733 --> 00:22:31,667
happy new year!

396
00:22:32,367 --> 00:22:33,567
Did you eat?

397
00:22:34,867 --> 00:22:35,467
Yes.

398
00:22:38,467 --> 00:22:39,633
I had jiaozi.

399
00:22:40,767 --> 00:22:41,367
Jia

400
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:43,600
say hello to Jiang.

401
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:45,233
Hello.

402
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:49,033
There were years when I didn't even know

403
00:22:49,033 --> 00:22:50,200
what the meaning of the Spring Festival was.

404
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:52,267
I made a lot of dishes

405
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:53,333
for the Spring Festival Eve.

406
00:22:53,867 --> 00:22:55,267
Have a taste of these.

407
00:22:55,267 --> 00:22:55,867
Eat as much as you can.

408
00:22:55,867 --> 00:22:57,367
There are more if not enough.

409
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,433
More dishes are to be served.

410
00:22:58,433 --> 00:23:00,067
Eat as much as you can, Jia.

411
00:23:00,067 --> 00:23:01,133
Eat some more, Fan.

412
00:23:01,133 --> 00:23:01,867
Eat the dishes.

413
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:06,000
It's my house.

414
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,067
I have the final say!

415
00:23:07,167 --> 00:23:08,133
I don't want her

416
00:23:08,133 --> 00:23:09,433
to eat at the table!

417
00:23:11,167 --> 00:23:12,433
What did you promise me?

418
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:13,833
Can't you just bear with it a bit?

419
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:16,700
Fan

420
00:23:17,767 --> 00:23:18,533
just eat.

421
00:23:24,233 --> 00:23:24,833
Zheng

422
00:23:25,333 --> 00:23:26,600
say hello to Jiang.

423
00:23:27,633 --> 00:23:28,767
Hello, Fan.

424
00:23:29,367 --> 00:23:30,067
Hello.

425
00:23:31,033 --> 00:23:32,600
Well, say a little more.

426
00:23:33,633 --> 00:23:34,367
Fan

427
00:23:34,767 --> 00:23:35,933
happy new year.

428
00:23:36,067 --> 00:23:38,200
Come home when you are free.

429
00:23:39,367 --> 00:23:40,367
Yeah.

430
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:43,333
Jiang

431
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:45,367
were you at work during the day?

432
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:46,833
You must be tired.

433
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:47,600
Go to bed early.

434
00:23:48,067 --> 00:23:49,433
I'll hang up now. Bye.

435
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,167
Why didn't you

436
00:24:10,067 --> 00:24:12,333
wish your parents a happy new year or else?

437
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:20,367
Isn't it always like this?

438
00:24:21,233 --> 00:24:22,900
My parents don't care much about me.

439
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,600
I fell asleep accidentally.

440
00:25:02,467 --> 00:25:03,833
Did they sing Unforgettable Tonight?

441
00:25:06,167 --> 00:25:07,400
The chorus is coming soon.

442
00:25:09,133 --> 00:25:10,000
Do you want to sing together?

443
00:25:11,567 --> 00:25:12,200
Okay.

444
00:25:12,533 --> 00:25:13,267
You go first.

445
00:25:14,167 --> 00:25:14,800
You wish!

446
00:25:24,133 --> 00:25:24,767
Dian.

447
00:25:26,133 --> 00:25:26,933
Come on. Time for bed.

448
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:31,667
I'm going to bed now.

449
00:25:33,467 --> 00:25:34,033
Good night.

450
00:25:44,833 --> 00:25:45,767
Happy New Year.

451
00:25:55,467 --> 00:25:56,367
Happy New Year.

452
00:26:15,667 --> 00:26:17,233
You uncle doesn't have a son.

453
00:26:19,367 --> 00:26:19,933
Enough.

454
00:26:23,700 --> 00:26:24,433
Jiang.

455
00:26:26,433 --> 00:26:27,067
Jiang.

456
00:26:29,933 --> 00:26:32,733
[Memorial Tablet of My Father Wen Liangzhe]

457
00:26:43,367 --> 00:26:44,433
Don't be too sad.

458
00:26:52,700 --> 00:26:54,200
What's your arrangement

459
00:26:55,900 --> 00:26:57,467
for Yifan in the future?

460
00:27:06,233 --> 00:27:07,633
Could you please

461
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:10,333
let her live with you?

462
00:27:10,533 --> 00:27:11,767
How about asking her to live with your mother-in-law?

463
00:27:12,067 --> 00:27:13,667
After all, she's her grandma. What do you think?

464
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:15,633
You're still young.

465
00:27:15,900 --> 00:27:17,400
It's not easy to take a child with you.

466
00:27:18,767 --> 00:27:20,433
Think about it, won't you?

467
00:27:47,900 --> 00:27:50,900
♪Listening to the rain falling on the pane♪

468
00:27:51,833 --> 00:27:54,667
♪How are you feeling♪

469
00:27:56,067 --> 00:27:59,867
♪Soft or peacuful♪

470
00:28:01,467 --> 00:28:02,233
Grandma!

471
00:28:02,267 --> 00:28:03,033
Yifan!

472
00:28:04,067 --> 00:28:06,433
♪In the damp, I smell♪

473
00:28:06,433 --> 00:28:08,067
I'll pick you up when I settle down.

474
00:28:08,167 --> 00:28:10,667
♪The base note of tears♪

475
00:28:12,133 --> 00:28:16,133
♪Is it warmth or burn♪

476
00:28:18,433 --> 00:28:20,333
♪The rain falls down♪

477
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:24,500
♪Accidently, I linger no more♪

478
00:28:24,767 --> 00:28:28,433
♪Just thinking about you, smiling♪

479
00:28:28,867 --> 00:28:31,767
♪It's a piece of azure youth♪

480
00:28:34,467 --> 00:28:35,133
Shuangjiang

481
00:28:35,233 --> 00:28:37,133
your grandma can't look after you in the future.

482
00:28:37,433 --> 00:28:38,833
Come live with me.

483
00:28:40,867 --> 00:28:44,833
♪I can't see the pure white back then♪

484
00:28:45,067 --> 00:28:48,367
♪ Probably because you are not here♪

485
00:28:51,333 --> 00:28:52,767
Jiang, come on, time for lunch.

486
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,400
If you don't want to live with me

487
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,433
call your mother frequently

488
00:28:58,767 --> 00:29:00,633
and ask her to pick you up soon, all right?

489
00:29:00,633 --> 00:29:01,133
Mom!

490
00:29:01,367 --> 00:29:01,867
Mom!

491
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:43,400
Hi. Twenty yuan.

492
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:47,867
Twenty.

493
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:51,067
Where is the money my aunt gave me?

494
00:29:52,033 --> 00:29:53,333
Will you buy it or not?

495
00:29:53,433 --> 00:29:54,567
People are waiting in line.

496
00:29:56,933 --> 00:29:57,667
I'm sorry.

497
00:29:57,667 --> 00:29:59,033
My money seems to be lost.

498
00:30:01,267 --> 00:30:02,633
How could it be lost?

499
00:30:04,067 --> 00:30:04,933
Will I be sent

500
00:30:04,933 --> 00:30:06,567
to somewhere else again?

501
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,333
Wen Shuangjiang.

502
00:30:30,067 --> 00:30:31,133
What are you doing sitting here?

503
00:30:41,900 --> 00:30:44,067
Why are you wearing this expression?

504
00:30:50,533 --> 00:30:52,433
Can you lend me twenty yuan?

505
00:31:00,433 --> 00:31:02,367
I came to play basketball

506
00:31:02,667 --> 00:31:03,533
and didn't bring any money.

507
00:31:04,633 --> 00:31:05,400
Don't bother.

508
00:31:06,167 --> 00:31:07,033
Bother with what?

509
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:09,667
That I don't have money now

510
00:31:09,667 --> 00:31:11,367
doesn't mean I won't have money in five minutes.

511
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:12,767
Take it.

512
00:31:14,700 --> 00:31:15,467
Take it.

513
00:31:18,367 --> 00:31:19,167
Wait for me here.

514
00:31:19,267 --> 00:31:19,933
Five minutes.

515
00:31:20,333 --> 00:31:21,067
Just five minutes.

516
00:31:21,233 --> 00:31:21,933
Wait for me.

517
00:31:43,833 --> 00:31:44,433
Here.

518
00:31:48,900 --> 00:31:49,600
Take it.

519
00:31:51,267 --> 00:31:53,267
You can give me back when you want.

520
00:31:54,333 --> 00:31:55,000
Thank you.

521
00:31:56,767 --> 00:31:57,667
What?

522
00:31:58,867 --> 00:32:00,367
It looks like you are about to cry.

523
00:32:02,900 --> 00:32:04,267
You don't have to be so touched.

524
00:32:05,367 --> 00:32:07,033
Well, it's not a big deal.

525
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:09,033
It's just that you lost twenty yuan.

526
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,767
Just call me

527
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:14,000
if you lose money again.

528
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:29,933
I can lend you

529
00:32:31,867 --> 00:32:32,700
however much you want.

530
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:11,933
Coming.

531
00:33:17,267 --> 00:33:18,067
Qiao?

532
00:33:18,433 --> 00:33:19,533
- Dian! - Xiang Lang?

533
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:21,333
Happy New Year!

534
00:33:21,767 --> 00:33:24,433
Happy New Year, Dian!

535
00:33:27,233 --> 00:33:28,267
Long time no see.

536
00:33:28,633 --> 00:33:29,200
See?

537
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:30,833
We are here to wish you a happy new year on the first day of the year.

538
00:33:30,833 --> 00:33:31,567
Are you surprised?

539
00:33:31,567 --> 00:33:32,167
Are you shocked?

540
00:33:32,167 --> 00:33:33,367
I'm surprised and shocked.

541
00:33:33,367 --> 00:33:33,933
Please come in.

542
00:33:33,933 --> 00:33:34,467
Okay.

543
00:33:35,167 --> 00:33:36,467
This is Dian's new home.

544
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:39,233
Is this Sang Yan's room?

545
00:33:40,067 --> 00:33:40,667
Qiao!

546
00:33:40,767 --> 00:33:42,033
Qiao, this is someone else's room.

547
00:33:42,033 --> 00:33:42,833
Let's not go in.

548
00:33:42,900 --> 00:33:43,900
Why are you so nervous?

549
00:33:45,133 --> 00:33:45,833
We...

550
00:33:46,233 --> 00:33:47,167
We have an agreement

551
00:33:47,167 --> 00:33:48,933
to tell each other in advance if other people come.

552
00:33:49,433 --> 00:33:50,867
We are other people?

553
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:54,400
Look, I bought you a New Year's gift.

554
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:56,067
We often fought over it when we were kids.

555
00:33:56,133 --> 00:33:57,367
She saw this at the store downstairs

556
00:33:57,367 --> 00:33:58,767
and couldn't even walk.

557
00:33:58,767 --> 00:34:00,133
I knew she wanted to eat this.

558
00:34:00,167 --> 00:34:01,000
Not like that!

559
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:01,600
It's the first day of the Spring Festival.

560
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:03,600
I'm bringing love to home...

561
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:04,867
To share it.

562
00:34:04,900 --> 00:34:06,633
You two are so harmonious now.

563
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:08,300
- Give it to me! Come on. - Let's go.

564
00:34:10,700 --> 00:34:12,600
I need to use the bathroom, Dian.

565
00:34:13,133 --> 00:34:14,133
It's Sang Yan's.

566
00:34:14,267 --> 00:34:15,233
Go to the one in my room.

567
00:34:15,433 --> 00:34:16,233
I'll use Sang Yan's.

568
00:34:16,233 --> 00:34:17,367
We are both boys. He won't mind.

569
00:34:18,667 --> 00:34:19,833
He will.

570
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:21,567
Here, eat this.

571
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:27,567
Do you have poker cards?

572
00:34:27,567 --> 00:34:28,367
Let's play poker!

573
00:34:28,967 --> 00:34:29,700
I'll get them.

574
00:34:31,667 --> 00:34:32,967
Wait a minute. I need to answer a call.

575
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:34,567
Where are they? I'll get them.

576
00:34:36,833 --> 00:34:37,700
There

577
00:34:38,167 --> 00:34:40,033
in the drawer of my dressing table.

578
00:34:40,267 --> 00:34:40,767
Okay.

579
00:34:46,700 --> 00:34:47,200
Hello?

580
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,033
You are awake?

581
00:34:49,667 --> 00:34:50,600
What are you calling me for?

582
00:34:50,833 --> 00:34:52,567
I bought too much porridge this morning.

583
00:34:52,700 --> 00:34:53,700
It's in the rice cooker.

584
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:54,467
Help eat some.

585
00:34:56,267 --> 00:34:57,567
I didn't know Sang Yan was so neat.

586
00:34:57,933 --> 00:34:59,167
The bathroom is neatly arranged.

587
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:05,367
Dian

588
00:35:06,300 --> 00:35:07,467
I can't find the poker cards.

589
00:35:07,467 --> 00:35:08,133
Look for them yourself.

590
00:35:08,133 --> 00:35:09,300
Okay, I'll get them for you later.

591
00:35:09,767 --> 00:35:10,433
There are other people.

592
00:35:10,767 --> 00:35:11,333
Yes.

593
00:35:11,333 --> 00:35:13,367
Well, Qiao came to wish me a happy new year.

594
00:35:13,367 --> 00:35:14,267
You called me

595
00:35:14,267 --> 00:35:15,167
when I was about to call you.

596
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:16,167
There's a guy too.

597
00:35:18,167 --> 00:35:19,367
Xiang Lang is here too.

598
00:35:21,867 --> 00:35:22,467
Eat this.

599
00:35:24,733 --> 00:35:25,933
Hello? Are you listening?

600
00:35:27,833 --> 00:35:28,767
It's too noisy here.

601
00:35:28,767 --> 00:35:29,567
I can't hear clearly.

602
00:35:30,267 --> 00:35:31,233
Talk later when I'm back.

603
00:35:32,367 --> 00:35:32,867
Hello?

604
00:35:38,867 --> 00:35:40,233
Is it noisy?

605
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:42,700
I'm dead!

606
00:35:51,367 --> 00:35:52,267
What should I do?

607
00:35:52,367 --> 00:35:53,400
He's killing his way back!

608
00:35:55,967 --> 00:35:58,400
Aren't we supposed to watch movies and play cards at home?

609
00:35:58,667 --> 00:36:00,267
Where are we going when it's so cold?

610
00:36:02,233 --> 00:36:02,800
Dian?

611
00:36:04,533 --> 00:36:06,800
We should take a walk outside during the festival.

612
00:36:10,200 --> 00:36:12,300
Anyway, I haven't been home for a long time

613
00:36:12,633 --> 00:36:13,700
and want to take a walk.

614
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:15,200
How about

615
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:16,433
going to somewhere far away?

616
00:36:16,567 --> 00:36:17,300
Good!

617
00:36:18,033 --> 00:36:19,667
But I can't go home too late.

618
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:22,467
Dian

619
00:36:22,933 --> 00:36:23,767
something's wrong with you.

620
00:36:24,267 --> 00:36:25,967
Are you afraid of Sang Yan?

621
00:36:26,133 --> 00:36:27,233
What does it have to do with Sang Yan?

622
00:36:27,767 --> 00:36:29,933
One thing in the joint rent agreement

623
00:36:29,933 --> 00:36:30,933
between Dian and Sang Yan

624
00:36:31,033 --> 00:36:32,567
is both of them can't take friends home for fun.

625
00:36:32,567 --> 00:36:33,767
And they can't go home too late.

626
00:36:33,767 --> 00:36:35,033
Don't be so exaggerate.

627
00:36:37,467 --> 00:36:38,233
Is Sang Yan

628
00:36:38,533 --> 00:36:40,033
usually very fierce to you?

629
00:36:40,167 --> 00:36:41,400
Why do I feel you fear him?

630
00:36:41,567 --> 00:36:43,433
No, don't listen to Qiao's overstatement.

631
00:36:43,667 --> 00:36:45,133
Why should I fear him?

632
00:36:45,267 --> 00:36:46,600
If it's not fear

633
00:36:47,433 --> 00:36:48,067
it's...

634
00:36:48,300 --> 00:36:48,967
care?

635
00:36:50,433 --> 00:36:51,267
Anyway, what we are doing

636
00:36:51,267 --> 00:36:52,467
is quite fun.

637
00:36:52,467 --> 00:36:54,433
It's like we are playing PVP in a game

638
00:36:54,667 --> 00:36:55,967
and we keep provoking

639
00:36:55,967 --> 00:36:57,033
our opponent.

640
00:36:57,033 --> 00:36:58,567
Then he got angry

641
00:36:58,567 --> 00:36:59,467
and picked up the sword.

642
00:37:00,233 --> 00:37:01,367
[Sweeping Thousands of Troops]

643
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:06,133
Since we're running for life

644
00:37:06,133 --> 00:37:06,700
get yourselves seated.

645
00:37:06,967 --> 00:37:08,433
Let's escape from that big monster.

646
00:37:08,433 --> 00:37:09,000
Okay.

647
00:37:14,267 --> 00:37:15,300
You've driven for so long.

648
00:37:15,300 --> 00:37:17,067
Is this the splendid scenery you talked about?

649
00:37:17,467 --> 00:37:18,700
I've been here when I was a kid.

650
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:20,867
It is beautiful.

651
00:37:21,233 --> 00:37:22,867
It's so cold.

652
00:37:22,867 --> 00:37:24,400
The coldness is giving me a headache.

653
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:31,167
I think it's beautiful.

654
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:32,833
Do you know

655
00:37:33,567 --> 00:37:35,033
legend has it there is a fairy?

656
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:36,700
She can make your wish come true

657
00:37:36,700 --> 00:37:37,700
if you make a wish to her.

658
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:38,700
Where is she?

659
00:37:39,267 --> 00:37:40,133
Over there.

660
00:37:40,700 --> 00:37:41,767
In the illusory.

661
00:37:45,267 --> 00:37:46,133
I need to answer a call.

662
00:37:47,167 --> 00:37:48,367
You are busy even in the Spring Festival.

663
00:37:49,667 --> 00:37:50,567
I have an order.

664
00:37:51,167 --> 00:37:52,367
It's not easy for us to meet.

665
00:37:52,567 --> 00:37:53,400
You should have powered it off.

666
00:37:54,067 --> 00:37:55,433
I took the order before the Spring Festival.

667
00:37:55,433 --> 00:37:56,367
I'll answer it.

668
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:06,700
Dian

669
00:38:08,133 --> 00:38:09,133
what's your wish?

670
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:16,433
Forget it.

671
00:38:17,200 --> 00:38:19,033
No wish can be truly realized.

672
00:38:24,333 --> 00:38:24,900
Hello?

673
00:38:24,900 --> 00:38:25,467
Hello?

674
00:38:25,867 --> 00:38:26,467
Zhong Siqiao

675
00:38:27,200 --> 00:38:29,200
I was wondering if we should rehearse for it.

676
00:38:29,467 --> 00:38:30,467
Rehearse?

677
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:32,300
More like a discussion.

678
00:38:35,467 --> 00:38:37,800
Isn't it just helping you by having dinner with you?

679
00:38:38,033 --> 00:38:38,867
Please!

680
00:38:39,700 --> 00:38:40,400
Where are you?

681
00:38:40,967 --> 00:38:41,567
At work.

682
00:38:42,200 --> 00:38:43,367
Okay, I got it.

683
00:38:43,867 --> 00:38:44,667
Okay, it's a deal.

684
00:38:44,667 --> 00:38:45,167
Bye.

685
00:38:47,033 --> 00:38:47,800
You don't have to.

686
00:38:47,967 --> 00:38:48,600
It's fine.

687
00:38:49,833 --> 00:38:50,433
Put it on.

688
00:39:04,367 --> 00:39:05,133
I'm leaving.

689
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:09,300
Did you catch a cold?

690
00:39:09,867 --> 00:39:11,000
Seems like it.

691
00:39:11,033 --> 00:39:12,400
I said you caught a cold and you didn't believe it.

692
00:39:13,167 --> 00:39:14,433
Here, take the cold medicine.

693
00:39:15,167 --> 00:39:15,867
Thank you.

694
00:39:16,633 --> 00:39:17,467
[Cold Remedy Granular]
Take it when you are back.

695
00:39:17,867 --> 00:39:18,533
Okay.

696
00:39:19,300 --> 00:39:20,633
You are only here to take an order?

697
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:22,433
Yes, the client made an appointment to discuss it here.

698
00:39:23,433 --> 00:39:24,233
Remember to take medicine.

699
00:39:24,233 --> 00:39:25,600
OK, stay safe.

700
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:26,467
- Bye. - Bye.

701
00:39:26,767 --> 00:39:27,400
Bye.

702
00:39:46,500 --> 00:39:48,000
[Uptown Flower City]

703
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,133
Hello, Qiao?

704
00:39:49,133 --> 00:39:50,933
You arrived home so early?

705
00:39:51,533 --> 00:39:52,133
We just arrived.

706
00:39:52,267 --> 00:39:53,633
I'm still in Xiang Lang's car.

707
00:39:54,967 --> 00:39:56,667
Did you go somewhere else?

708
00:39:58,933 --> 00:39:59,833
Well...

709
00:40:01,067 --> 00:40:02,000
What do you want to say?

710
00:40:03,367 --> 00:40:04,767
Can you please help me check

711
00:40:04,767 --> 00:40:06,167
if Sang Yan is still working?

712
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:10,933
He doesn't seem to be here.

713
00:40:11,967 --> 00:40:12,567
What's wrong?

714
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:14,433
You are afraid to meet him when you are back home.

715
00:40:14,767 --> 00:40:15,800
Of course not.

716
00:40:16,367 --> 00:40:17,400
Okay, that's it.

717
00:40:19,233 --> 00:40:20,367
Shall I go upstairs with you?

718
00:40:21,633 --> 00:40:22,767
Let's go eat something.

719
00:40:22,767 --> 00:40:23,400
Are you hungry?

720
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:25,433
Well, Qiao

721
00:40:25,700 --> 00:40:26,800
we are going to eat something.

722
00:40:26,833 --> 00:40:27,833
Take time with your work.

723
00:40:28,833 --> 00:40:29,533
Okay.

724
00:40:29,533 --> 00:40:31,233
Then you go and eat.

725
00:40:31,533 --> 00:40:32,167
Bye!

726
00:40:32,400 --> 00:40:33,200
Okay, bye.

727
00:40:33,800 --> 00:40:34,767
Let's go eat casserole porridge.

728
00:40:35,167 --> 00:40:35,933
We've been in the cold the whole day.

729
00:40:35,933 --> 00:40:36,633
It will warm us.

730
00:40:39,267 --> 00:40:39,867
You are awake?

731
00:40:40,533 --> 00:40:41,433
What are you calling me for?

732
00:40:41,667 --> 00:40:43,400
I bought too much porridge this morning.

733
00:40:43,567 --> 00:40:44,567
It's in the rice cooker.

734
00:40:44,633 --> 00:40:45,300
Help eat some.

735
00:40:45,833 --> 00:40:47,233
Oh, no! The porridge!

736
00:40:48,067 --> 00:40:49,033
We can eat something else

737
00:40:49,033 --> 00:40:50,067
if you don't want it.

738
00:40:50,300 --> 00:40:51,000
It's not that.

739
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:52,200
We'll eat it some other day.

740
00:40:52,267 --> 00:40:53,367
Be careful on the road.

741
00:40:53,433 --> 00:40:54,233
Dian...

742
00:41:26,467 --> 00:41:27,200
What are you looking for?

743
00:41:29,667 --> 00:41:30,600
You're back.

744
00:41:32,133 --> 00:41:33,067
I was back at noon.

745
00:41:35,433 --> 00:41:36,200
I'm sorry.

746
00:41:36,233 --> 00:41:38,300
I forgot to eat the porridge you asked me to.

747
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:39,633
Why did you apologize?

748
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:42,400
Do you think

749
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:43,933
I bought the porridge for you especially?

750
00:41:49,167 --> 00:41:50,600
Who took off gloves

751
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:51,433
to insist

752
00:41:51,433 --> 00:41:53,000
that we can't bring other people home?

753
00:41:54,233 --> 00:41:54,800
Who was it?

754
00:41:57,667 --> 00:41:58,533
I'm sorry.

755
00:41:58,667 --> 00:42:00,167
I'll tell you in advance next time.

756
00:42:00,267 --> 00:42:00,933
Next time?

757
00:42:04,367 --> 00:42:06,233
Do you want to punish me?

758
00:42:10,233 --> 00:42:11,133
Okay, punishment.

759
00:42:12,367 --> 00:42:13,633
So what will be the punishment?

760
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:18,700
I don't know.

761
00:42:20,300 --> 00:42:21,200
It's up to you.

762
00:42:23,267 --> 00:42:24,567
If it's up to me

763
00:42:24,700 --> 00:42:25,667
then...

764
00:42:30,867 --> 00:42:31,533
Exchange.

765
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:33,200
Exchange for what?

766
00:42:35,567 --> 00:42:36,300
Tomorrow

767
00:42:36,533 --> 00:42:38,633
I'll take someone home for dinner too.

768
00:42:48,067 --> 00:42:49,133
Do you have a girlfriend?

769
00:42:52,533 --> 00:42:53,767
I mean

770
00:42:53,767 --> 00:42:54,967
you should tell your girlfriend

771
00:42:54,967 --> 00:42:56,533
about our joint rent

772
00:42:56,533 --> 00:42:57,600
if you have one

773
00:42:57,600 --> 00:42:58,800
in case of misunderstandings.

774
00:42:59,967 --> 00:43:00,800
I don't have a girlfriend.

775
00:43:01,267 --> 00:43:02,033
But

776
00:43:02,033 --> 00:43:03,300
don't be too happy about it.

777
00:43:03,700 --> 00:43:04,700
I don't want one.

778
00:43:06,867 --> 00:43:07,533
Okay.

779
00:43:08,033 --> 00:43:09,567
So we'll talk about it

780
00:43:09,567 --> 00:43:10,800
if you find a girlfriend

781
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:11,600
during our joint rent.

782
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:14,233
And of course

783
00:43:14,233 --> 00:43:16,300
I will tell you if I have a boyfriend.

784
00:43:16,300 --> 00:43:17,000
Not interested.

785
00:43:22,367 --> 00:43:23,767
Who is he going to bring back home?

786
00:43:26,900 --> 00:43:29,300
[Episode 6]
[I Will Always Be with You]

787
00:43:29,300 --> 00:43:31,500
[Episode 6]
[Will You Always Be with Me?]

788
00:43:44,267 --> 00:43:50,733
[The story is not over yet...]

789
00:43:51,067 --> 00:43:52,967
He usually eats very politely.

790
00:43:53,133 --> 00:43:53,633
Dad

791
00:43:54,067 --> 00:43:55,633
I think something's wrong

792
00:43:55,833 --> 00:43:56,467
with my brother.

793
00:43:57,933 --> 00:43:58,800
Your brother...

794
00:43:58,933 --> 00:43:59,667
Let's toast!

795
00:44:03,833 --> 00:44:04,367
Well, next...

796
00:44:04,367 --> 00:44:05,467
I have things to do. I'm going out.

797
00:44:06,133 --> 00:44:07,600
Where are you going on the Spring Festival Eve?

798
00:44:08,233 --> 00:44:09,033
To meet a friend.

799
00:44:09,033 --> 00:44:09,767
What friend?

800
00:44:09,767 --> 00:44:10,800
Is it Jiaxu?

801
00:44:12,367 --> 00:44:13,867
Meet him tomorrow even if you have to.

802
00:44:13,867 --> 00:44:15,267
It's the Spring Festival Eve.

803
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:16,300
Come on, Ping.

804
00:44:16,767 --> 00:44:17,833
It's the Spring Festival Eve.

805
00:44:20,467 --> 00:44:21,267
It's fine.

806
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:22,633
It's because you spoiled him.

807
00:44:25,867 --> 00:44:26,867
Why are you back?

808
00:44:27,867 --> 00:44:30,267
Didn't you said you wouldn't be back until the eighth day of Spring Festival?

809
00:44:31,000 --> 00:44:32,533
Too many relatives at home.

810
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:33,400
There are not enough rooms.

811
00:44:40,167 --> 00:44:41,500
♪Even the strongest heart♪

812
00:44:41,667 --> 00:44:43,333
♪Can waver♪

813
00:44:43,567 --> 00:44:46,767
♪And doubt its fire♪

814
00:44:47,033 --> 00:44:48,667
♪But you never lost faith in me♪

815
00:44:48,667 --> 00:44:50,333
♪In every battle, every dream I chased♪

816
00:44:50,533 --> 00:44:53,233
♪There is meaning in every step I made♪

817
00:44:54,067 --> 00:45:00,033
♪Through the storm, through the endless night♪

818
00:45:00,367 --> 00:45:02,033
♪You were there, shining like a light♪

819
00:45:02,033 --> 00:45:03,700
♪Warm and bright♪

820
00:45:03,867 --> 00:45:07,567
♪Standing right by my side♪

821
00:45:08,033 --> 00:45:14,133
♪It was you, striding toward me through the storm♪

822
00:45:14,500 --> 00:45:21,433
♪It was you, always cheering me on♪

823
00:45:21,567 --> 00:45:24,567
♪The road is rough♪

824
00:45:24,900 --> 00:45:29,033
♪The rain won't stop♪

825
00:45:29,233 --> 00:45:33,167
♪But with you here♪

826
00:45:33,467 --> 00:45:39,500
♪I fear no dark♪

827
00:45:42,733 --> 00:45:46,333
♪Every thought, every memory is filled with you♪

828
00:45:46,667 --> 00:45:50,133
♪Marking our youth with every step we took♪

829
00:45:50,433 --> 00:45:52,300
♪When the downpour falls from the sky♪

830
00:45:52,300 --> 00:45:55,933
♪You're the one holding out an umbrella for me♪

831
00:45:56,300 --> 00:45:59,867
♪When the white dove brings the news♪

832
00:46:00,233 --> 00:46:03,667
♪You're the first I want to tell♪

833
00:46:04,067 --> 00:46:12,700
♪I won't give up. I'll stay right here with you♪

834
00:46:17,300 --> 00:46:23,500
♪It was you, striding toward me through the storm♪

835
00:46:24,333 --> 00:46:30,767
♪It was you, always cheering me on♪

836
00:46:30,767 --> 00:46:33,933
♪The road is rough♪

837
00:46:34,433 --> 00:46:38,367
♪The rain won't stop♪

838
00:46:38,567 --> 00:46:41,233
♪But with you here♪

839
00:46:41,433 --> 00:46:45,267
♪I will never give up♪

840
00:46:45,533 --> 00:46:51,633
♪You are my courage, my hope for the sky beyond♪

841
00:46:52,133 --> 00:46:57,967
♪You are my light, shining through every night♪

842
00:46:58,533 --> 00:47:01,367
♪Even if I have to walk alone someday♪

843
00:47:01,833 --> 00:47:04,667
♪I'll never truly be on my own♪

844
00:47:05,700 --> 00:47:10,233
♪'Cause knowing you're here♪

845
00:47:10,667 --> 00:47:17,267
♪I can brave the dark ahead♪

846
00:47:19,067 --> 00:47:20,333
[Huge thanks to everyone involved and to all the fans of The First Frost!]
